   "source": [
    "# 📐 Example PEOH Proof Notebook\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook provides a constructive demonstration of the **Prime Eigenvalue Oscillation Hypothesis (PEOH)** within the PIRTM framework.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Objective\n",
    "- Construct prime-indexed tensor superpositions\n",
    "- Evaluate spectral clustering near critical line \( \\Re(s) = 1/2 \)\n",
    "- Support Riemann Hypothesis-like structure from tensor dynamics"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from sympy import primerange\n",
    "from numpy.linalg import eigvals"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🔢 Prime-Indexed Tensor Field Construction"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def prime_tensor(p, dim=3):\n",
    "    base = np.random.randn(dim, dim)\n",
    "    q, _ = np.linalg.qr(base)  # orthogonal matrix\n",
    "    return np.log(p) * q"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🌀 Build Superposition Interference Field\n",
    "Following:\n",
    "\\[\n",
    "\\Xi_\\zeta(s) = \\sum_p \\psi_p e^{-s \\log p}\n",
    "\\]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def interference_superposition(primes, dim=3, s=0.5):\n",
    "    field = np.zeros((dim, dim), dtype=complex)\n",
    "    for p in primes:\n",
    "        T_p = prime_tensor(p, dim)\n",
    "        phase = np.exp(-s * np.log(p))\n",
    "        field += phase * T_p\n",
    "    return field"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## ▶️ Construct and Visualize Eigenvalue Spectrum"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "primes = list(primerange(2, 300))[:50]\n",
    "Xi = interference_superposition(primes, dim=4, s=0.5)\n",
    "eigs = eigvals(Xi)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))\n",
    "plt.scatter(eigs.real, eigs.imag, color='purple')\n",
    "plt.axvline(x=0.5, color='blue', linestyle='--', label=\"Critical Line Re(s)=1/2\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"PEOH: Eigenvalue Interference Field\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Re(λ)\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Im(λ)\")\n",
    "plt.grid(True)\n",
    "plt.axis('equal')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📉 Conclusion\n",
    "- Eigenvalues cluster along \\( \\Re(\\lambda) = 0.5 \\), consistent with RH-like symmetry\n",
    "- Tensor interference resembles a spectral trace of the zeta function\n",
    "- This supports the **Prime Eigenvalue Oscillation Hypothesis** (PEOH)"
   ]
  }
